## Project conventions — read first

Before answering or editing code, read the files in
`{{ ai_folder }}/instructions/`. They are authoritative — if anything
in this file conflicts, they win.

**General (always):**

- `general/coding-conventions.md` — language-agnostic style and idioms
- `general/architecture.md` — DDD layering rules
- `general/ddd.md` — domain modelling (entities, value objects, aggregates, repos, UoW)
- `general/tdd.md` — test-driven micro-implementation
- `general/testing.md` — what / where / how to test
- `general/security.md` — security posture
{% if 'python' in languages %}
**Python (when touching Python):**

- `python/zen.md` — PEP 20
- `python/style.md` — formatting, type hints, docstrings
- `python/tooling.md` — `uv`, `ruff`, `mypy`, `pytest`
- `python/design.md` — composition, DI, protocols, properties vs methods
- `python/patterns.md` — value objects, policy, context object, unit of work
- `python/code-smells.md` — refactor against this taxonomy
- `python/testing.md` — pytest, hypothesis, mutation, classical school
{% endif %}{% if 'rust' in languages %}
**Rust (when touching Rust):**

- `rust/style.md` — naming, edition, error handling (thiserror / anyhow), lints
- `rust/tooling.md` — cargo, clippy, rustfmt, useful subcommands
- `rust/design.md` — ownership, traits, type-state, make-invalid-states-unrepresentable
- `rust/patterns.md` — newtype, builder, RAII guards, enum dispatch, Cow
- `rust/code-smells.md` — `.unwrap()`, gratuitous `.clone()`, `Box<dyn>` over generics
- `rust/testing.md` — `#[cfg(test)]`, proptest, criterion, cargo-nextest
{% endif %}{% if 'typescript' in languages %}
**TypeScript (when touching TS):**

- `typescript/style.md` — strict mode, naming, no-any, branded types
- `typescript/tooling.md` — npm/pnpm, tsc, Biome, Vitest
- `typescript/design.md` — discriminated unions, branded types, exhaustive matching
- `typescript/patterns.md` — Result, policy, exhaustive switch, DI, schema-validated boundaries
- `typescript/code-smells.md` — `any`, bag-of-optionals, floating promises, `enum` abuse
- `typescript/testing.md` — Vitest, fast-check, classical school
{% endif %}{% if 'cpp' in languages %}
**C/C++ (when touching C/C++):**

- `cpp/style.md` — C++20, naming, headers, smart pointers, error handling
- `cpp/tooling.md` — CMake presets, vcpkg/Conan, sanitisers, clang-tidy
- `cpp/design.md` — RAII, value semantics, ownership in types, concepts, composition
- `cpp/patterns.md` — strong types, RAII guards, variant+visit, concepts, PIMPL, NVI
- `cpp/code-smells.md` — raw new/delete, C-style casts, slicing, default args on virtuals
- `cpp/testing.md` — GoogleTest / Catch2, fixtures, parametrize, rapidcheck, sanitisers
{% endif %}
## Working style

- **Micro-implementation is test-driven** (red-green-refactor). See `general/tdd.md`.
- **Design is DDD**: ubiquitous language, layering, pure domain. See `general/ddd.md`.
{% if 'python' in languages %}- **Python runs through `uv`** — never `python`, `pip`, `poetry`, `virtualenv` directly. Always `uv run ...`, `uv add ...`. See `python/tooling.md`.
{% endif %}- **Skills** in `{{ ai_folder }}/skills/`: `tdd-cycle`, `design-review`, `refactor-code-smell`, `lint-and-format`, `run-tests`{% if 'python' in languages %}, `python-uv-setup`{% endif %}.
- **Subagents** in `{{ ai_folder }}/agents/`: `code-reviewer`, `ddd-architect`, `tdd-driver`{% if 'python' in languages %}, `python-refactorer`{% endif %}.

## Source layout

```
src/application/      Use cases, services, orchestration
src/domain/           Pure business logic (entities, value objects, interfaces)
src/infrastructure/   DB, network, drivers, external adapters
src/presentation/     Entry points (HTTP routers, CLI, ISRs)
tests/{unit,integration,e2e,performance}
```

Empty directories are prefixed with `_` until they receive their first file.

